    <h2 id="ovens">Bakery Ovens — Types, Uses & Prices in India</h2>

    <p>The oven is the heart of every bakery. The right bakery machine for baking depends on what you produce — breads need deck ovens, pastries work best in convection ovens, and high-volume operations demand rotary rack ovens. Here's the breakdown of every oven type with India 2026 pricing.</p>

    <h3>Convection Oven</h3>
    <p>A convection oven uses fans to circulate hot air evenly around the baking chamber. It's the most popular bakery machine for small to mid-sized bakeries in India because it handles cookies, cakes, pastries, and breads reasonably well.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>4-tray convection oven:</strong> ₹45,000 – ₹1,50,000</li>
      <li><strong>6-tray convection oven:</strong> ₹80,000 – ₹2,20,000</li>
      <li><strong>8-10 tray convection oven:</strong> ₹1,20,000 – ₹3,50,000</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Small bakeries, cake shops, patisseries, and multi-product bakeries producing cakes, cookies, and muffins.</p>

    <h3>Deck Oven</h3>
    <p>A deck oven bakes directly on a stone or steel deck with heat from above and below. Artisan bread bakers swear by deck ovens because the radiant heat creates a superior crust. The bakery machine price for deck ovens is higher than convection but worth it for bread-focused operations.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>1-deck, 2-tray deck oven:</strong> ₹60,000 – ₹1,80,000</li>
      <li><strong>2-deck, 4-tray deck oven:</strong> ₹1,20,000 – ₹3,20,000</li>
      <li><strong>3-deck, 9-tray deck oven:</strong> ₹2,00,000 – ₹5,50,000</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Artisan bread bakeries, pizza shops, and bakeries that need precise top/bottom heat control.</p>

    <h3>Rotary Rack Oven</h3>
    <p>The rotary rack oven is the high-volume bakery machine. A rotating rack (typically 32 or 36 trays) ensures perfectly even baking across hundreds of products per batch. This is a serious investment — and a game-changer for wholesale and industrial bakeries.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>32-tray rotary rack oven (Indian):</strong> ₹5,00,000 – ₹8,00,000</li>
      <li><strong>36-tray rotary rack oven (imported):</strong> ₹8,00,000 – ₹12,00,000</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Wholesale bakeries, bread factories, large catering operations producing 500+ units per day.</p>

    <h3>Pizza Oven</h3>
    <p>If your bakery also produces pizza, a dedicated pizza oven is essential. Options range from affordable electric pizza ovens to premium stone-base gas ovens.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Electric pizza oven (single deck):</strong> ₹35,000 – ₹80,000</li>
      <li><strong>Gas pizza oven (stone base):</strong> ₹60,000 – ₹1,50,000</li>
      <li><strong>Wood-fired pizza oven:</strong> ₹1,00,000 – ₹2,50,000</li>
    </ul>

    <p>For a detailed comparison of all oven types with brand recommendations, read our complete <a href="/blog/bakery-oven-price-india">bakery oven prices</a> guide and the <a href="/blog/oven-for-bakery-price-india">oven price list</a>. Also see our guide on <a href="/blog/gas-vs-electric-oven-bakery">gas vs electric ovens</a> and <a href="/blog/deck-oven-vs-convection-oven">deck oven vs convection oven</a>. Browse all bakery ovens in our <a href="/bakery-ovens">bakery ovens category</a>.</p>

