    <h2 id="mixers">Mixers — Planetary, Spiral & Dough Kneaders with Prices</h2>

    <p>After the oven, the mixer is the second most important bakery machine. You'll likely need at least one — and many bakeries use two different types. Understanding the difference between planetary mixers, spiral mixers, and simple dough kneaders is crucial before you buy.</p>

    <h3>Planetary Mixer</h3>
    <p>A planetary mixer is the most versatile bakery machine for mixing. The attachment rotates on its own axis while orbiting the bowl — just like a planet orbiting the sun. This motion is perfect for whipping cream, beating eggs, mixing cake batters, and kneading light doughs.</p>

