    <h2 id="dough-processing">Dough Processing Machines — Sheeter, Divider, Rounder & Moulder</h2>

    <p>Once dough is mixed, it needs to be shaped. For small bakeries, hand-shaping works. But if you're producing 200+ bread loaves, 500+ buns, or rolling out puff pastry in bulk, dough processing machines save hours of labour and ensure consistency. Here's the bakery machine price for each type.</p>

    <h3>Dough Sheeter / Laminator</h3>
    <p>A dough sheeter rolls dough to a uniform thickness — essential for puff pastry, croissants, pizza bases, and laminated doughs. Without one, you're rolling by hand for hours.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Table-top dough sheeter (50-60 cm width):</strong> ₹55,000 – ₹1,50,000</li>
      <li><strong>Floor-standing dough sheeter (60-80 cm width):</strong> ₹1,50,000 – ₹4,00,000</li>
      <li><strong>Reversible automatic sheeter:</strong> ₹2,50,000 – ₹6,00,000</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Tip:</strong> If you produce croissants or puff pastry, a reversible sheeter pays for itself within months by saving labour. For smaller bakeries making only pizza bases, a table-top sheeter is sufficient.</p>

    <h3>Dough Divider</h3>
    <p>A dough divider cuts a large batch of dough into equal-weight portions. This bakery machine is critical for bread bakeries that need consistent loaf sizes.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Manual dough divider (20-36 portions):</strong> ₹70,000 – ₹1,20,000</li>
      <li><strong>Semi-automatic dough divider:</strong> ₹1,20,000 – ₹2,00,000</li>
      <li><strong>Automatic volumetric divider:</strong> ₹2,00,000 – ₹3,00,000</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Dough Rounder</h3>
    <p>After dividing, a dough rounder shapes each portion into a smooth ball. This step ensures uniform proofing and final baking. Dough rounders are paired with dividers in bread production lines.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Conical dough rounder:</strong> ₹80,000 – ₹1,50,000</li>
      <li><strong>Heavy-duty automatic rounder:</strong> ₹1,50,000 – ₹2,50,000</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Bread Moulder</h3>
    <p>A bread moulder takes rounded dough balls and shapes them into elongated loaf shapes — ready for panning and proofing. This bakery machine is essential for sandwich bread and Pullman loaf production.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Table-top moulder:</strong> ₹90,000 – ₹1,60,000</li>
      <li><strong>Floor-standing automatic moulder:</strong> ₹1,60,000 – ₹3,50,000</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Production line pricing:</strong> A complete dough divider + rounder + moulder line for a medium bread bakery costs ₹2,50,000 – ₹7,00,000 depending on automation level. For layout planning, see our <a href="/blog/bakery-kitchen-layout">bakery kitchen layout</a> guide.</p>

