    <h2 id="proofing">Proofing Equipment — Proofer Cabinet & Retarder-Proofer</h2>

    <p>Proofing is the final rise of yeast dough before baking. A controlled proofing environment (warm temperature + high humidity) ensures consistent results every time. Here's what each proofing bakery machine costs.</p>

    <h3>Proofer Cabinet</h3>
    <p>A proofer cabinet maintains temperature (typically 30-40°C) and humidity (75-85%) for optimal yeast fermentation. Every bread bakery needs one.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>16-tray proofer cabinet (Indian make):</strong> ₹40,000 – ₹80,000</li>
      <li><strong>32-tray proofer cabinet (Indian make):</strong> ₹75,000 – ₹1,30,000</li>
      <li><strong>32-tray proofer cabinet (imported):</strong> ₹1,20,000 – ₹1,80,000</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Retarder-Proofer</h3>
    <p>A retarder-proofer is a dual-function bakery machine — it chills dough overnight to slow fermentation (retarding), then automatically switches to proofing mode in the early morning so dough is ready to bake when you arrive. This is a luxury for small bakeries but essential for operations that want fresh bread ready at 6 AM without a 3 AM start.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Single-rack retarder-proofer (16-18 tray):</strong> ₹1,50,000 – ₹2,50,000</li>
      <li><strong>Double-rack retarder-proofer (32-36 tray):</strong> ₹2,50,000 – ₹5,00,000</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Budget tip:</strong> If a retarder-proofer is outside your budget, you can use a regular refrigerator for retarding and a basic proofer cabinet for proofing. The results won't be quite as consistent, but it works for smaller operations.</p>

