    <h2 id="weighing-measuring">Weighing & Measuring Instruments</h2>

    <p>Baking is a science — precision matters. A ₹500 scale pays for itself by preventing ingredient waste and ensuring consistent recipes. Every bakery needs at least two scales and a thermometer. Here's the bakery machine price for measuring instruments.</p>

    <h3>Digital Scales</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Commercial platform scale (15-30 kg, 1g accuracy):</strong> ₹1,500 – ₹5,000</li>
      <li><strong>Precision scale (3-5 kg, 0.1g accuracy):</strong> ₹800 – ₹3,000</li>
      <li><strong>Micro scale (200-500g, 0.01g accuracy):</strong> ₹500 – ₹2,500</li>
      <li><strong>Heavy-duty floor scale (100-300 kg):</strong> ₹5,000 – ₹15,000</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Pro tip:</strong> Buy a 0.1g precision scale even if you think you don't need it. Accurate measurement of yeast, salt, and baking powder makes a measurable difference in bread and cake quality.</p>

    <h3>Thermometers</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Digital probe thermometer:</strong> ₹300 – ₹1,500</li>
      <li><strong>Infrared (IR) thermometer:</strong> ₹500 – ₹2,500</li>
      <li><strong>Oven thermometer (hanging type):</strong> ₹200 – ₹800</li>
      <li><strong>Refrigerator/freezer thermometer:</strong> ₹150 – ₹600</li>
      <li><strong>Chocolate/sugar thermometer:</strong> ₹300 – ₹1,200</li>
    </ul>
    <p>A probe thermometer checks internal bread temperature (it should read 95-98°C when done). An IR thermometer quickly checks oven and surface temperatures without contact. An oven thermometer verifies that your oven's thermostat is accurate — most ovens are off by 10-20°C.</p>

    <h3>Timers</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Basic digital kitchen timer:</strong> ₹150 – ₹400</li>
      <li><strong>Triple timer (tracks 3 items):</strong> ₹300 – ₹800</li>
      <li><strong>Commercial multi-channel timer:</strong> ₹500 – ₹2,000</li>
    </ul>

